<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-05-26T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-05-26T16:00:00-05:00" n="699" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d699">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.8212a/4: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Walton</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-26T17:00:00-04:00">May 26, 1939—5
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>21. Your telegram no. 35, May 24, noon. The expenses would arise only
                                as and when the Commission is called upon to function.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>